usg:
Use to set whether input elements can by default have their values automatically filled by the browser based on previously typed in values.

It is possible to have autocomplete "on" for the form, and "off" for specific input fields, or vice versa.

vals.desc: The user must explicitly enter a value into each field for every use, or the document provides its own auto-completion method; the browser does not automatically complete entries.
The browser can automatically complete values based on values that the user has previously entered in the form.
